'''Ethylene Copolymer Bitumen''' ('''ECB''') is a black colored mixture based on high quality polyethylene copolymers with different proportions of various special and amorphous bitumen grades.

The ECB membrane (used for proofing) was invented in 1968.<ref>{{ro icon}}[http://www.revistaconstructiilor.eu/index.php/2008/11/30/icopal-membrane-hidroizolante-din-materiale-plastice/ ICOPAL: Membrane hidroizolante din materiale plastice], 30 noiembrie 2008, ''Revista Construcțiilor</ref>

