The '''Veszprém Wind Farm''' is an under construction wind power project in [[Veszprém (county)|Veszprém County]], [[Hungary]]. It will have 30 individual [[wind turbine]]s<ref>[http://www.ebrdrenewables.com/sites/renew/Lists/EBRD%20Master%20Spreadsheet/DispForm.aspx?ID=82&Source=http%3A%2F%2Febrdrenewables%2Ecom%2Fsites%2Frenew%2Fcountries%2FHungary%2Fdefault%2Easpx Irish-Based Group to Develop Wind Farm in Hungary]</ref> with a nominal output of around 2 [[Watt#Megawatt|MW]] which will deliver up to 60 [[Megawatt|MW]] of power, enough to power over 40,100 homes, with a capital investment required of approximately US$225 million.

